description:
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work as part of a team in delivering an effective service in supporting the functions of the CDAO and ensuring that statutory obligations relating to the that the CD Regulations are met.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be directly responsible for the delivery of specific programmes of work including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading members of the team as well as supporting effective communication and stakeholder management, both internally and externally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Co-ordinating Local Intelligence Network (LIN) meetings across the whole geography&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain the management of systems that monitor CD incidents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide assurance that subsequent actions are being monitored and undertaken.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse data received, identifying trends or anomalies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse NHS and private prescribing of CDs using electronic Prescribing Analysis and Cost (ePACT).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accurate and open communication and co-ordination with a range of organisations and individuals, researching and drafting correspondence and papers when necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJackie CampbellJob titleControlled Drugs Programme ManagerEmail addressjackie.campbell4@nhs.netTelephone number07900715460&lt;/p&gt;
